Entrezgene.Entrezgene_summary: This gene encodes a member of the major facilitator superfamily of transporter proteins. The encoded protein likely functions in efflux of organic anions, including the non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs indomethacin and diclofenac. Alternatively spliced transcript variants have been described. [provided by RefSeq, Mar 2009]

Gene-commentary.Gene-commentary_text: TETRAN is a novel human organic anion transporter, and that it serves as a transporter for some NSAIDs and various other organic anions at the final excretion step.

A BLAST search identified the possible human orthologue of Tpo1p, tetracycline transporter-like protein (TETRAN), whose overexpression in cultured human cells caused resistance to some NSAIDs, suggesting that TETRAN is an efflux pump for some NSAIDs.
Ubiquitous expression in bone marrow (RPKM 36.8), spleen (RPKM 13.5) and 24 other tissues
